I can see that we are not talking about the same thing here.  Yes multithreading 
depends on your OS obviously, but I am saying that how well your Multithreaded OS 
works depends heavily on the design of the motherboard.  No one is talking about a 
non SMP OS on a dual processor machine.  That would be stupid.  I believe you are 
talking about single application speeds which is not the topic here.  We are talking 
about overall SYSTEM speeds.  So whether your app is multithreaded or not, the 
processor will schedule tasks on the seperate CPU's if it is SMP.  Besides, a good 
or bad SMP OS design could be entirely based on the hardware.  Some SMP OS's do 
better on certain types of hardware setups.  

